<title>CANADA: Newbridge Networks in 2-for-1 stock split.</title>
<headline>Newbridge Networks in 2-for-1 stock split.</headline>
<dateline>TORONTO 1996-09-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>Newbridge Networks Corp said on Friday its board declared a two-for-one stock split which will take effect through a 100 percent stock dividend.</p>
<p>The dividend will be payable on October 11 to shareholders of record as of September 30.</p>
<p>Newbridge said after the stock split takes effect, there will be about 170 million shares outstanding. The company said the move is designed to encourage wider ownership and boost trading liquidity of Newbridge shares.</p>
<p>The stock was 3.70 higher at 93.50 on the Toronto Stock Exchange.</p>
<p>-- Reuters Toronto Bureau (416) 941-8100</p>
